com.github.arachnidium.model.interfaces

Interface IDecomposable

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    IDecomposableByHandles<U>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AndroidApp, AndroidNativeContent, Application, BrowserApplication, BrowserPage, FunctionalPart, IOSApp, iOSNativeContent, MobileApplication, ModelObject, NativeContent, WebViewContent

    public interface IDecomposable
    There is an assumption that any object (whole application, page/screen and so on) could be decomposed to limited set of logically final and reusable parts. This interface specifies decomposition model provided by Arachnidium Java framework.

      • getPart

        <T extends IDecomposable> T getPart(Class<T> partClass,
                                    HowToGetByFrames pathStrategy,
                                    org.openqa.selenium.By by)
        This method should provide the getting of more specific part from another which is more generalized. As it is all about UI of browser and mobile applications, the usage of frames is possible (browser applications, hybrid mobile clients). So this fact is considered by method.

        The root element is defined By locator strategy
        Parameters:
        partClass - is required class that implements IDecomposable
        pathStrategy - is a path to frame which is specified by HowToGetByFrames
        by - Is a locator strategy which is used to get the root WebElement
        Returns:
        The instance of required class specified by @param partClass
